The Message resource provides a way to send and retrieve messages for a list.

## Filters

Filters can be used to select contacts based on their profile data. They may be supplied when sending a message via the `Filter` field.

Filters may be combined and nested in nearly limitless combinations. A filter is considered valid if it either defines profile data to filter on, or if it defines one or more inner filters. It is not valid to do neither or both. If a filter is defining inner filters, its `Filters` field should be set to an array of one or more filters. Otherwise, it should specify a `CompareType`, a `SegmentationFieldGroup`, a `SegmentationField`, and if applicable, one or more `Values` to apply to filtering logic.

When defining multiple filters in a set, the second and subsequent filters must define how they should be joined to the preceding filter. This is specified using the `JoinType` field. Valid values are `And`, `AndNot`, `Or`, and `OrNot`. It is not necessary to specify a `JoinType` for the first (or only) filter in a set, because there is no other filter to join with.

Filtering logic is determined by the `CompareType` field. Below is a table of supported values, a brief description of each, and the number of values required for operation:

| CompareType | Description | Number of values required |
|-|-|-|
| `Between` | The field is between the range of the two specified values (inclusive). | 2 |
| `NotBetween` | The field is not between the range of the two specified values (inclusive). | 2 |
| `Contains` | The field contains the specified value. | 1 |
| `NotContains` | The field does not contain the specified value. | 1 |
| `Equals` | The field equals the specified value (case insensitive). | 1 |
| `NotEquals` | The field does not equal the specified value (case insensitive). | 1 |
| `GreaterThan` | The field is greater the specified value. | 1 |
| `GreaterThanOrEqualTo` | The field is greater than or equal to the specified value. | 1 |
| `LessThan` | The field is less than the specified value. | 1 |
| `LessThanOrEqualTo` | The field is less than or equal to the specified value. | 1 |
| `InCommaList` | The field is one of the specified values in a comma-separated list. | 1 |
| `NotInCommaList` | The field is not one of the specified values in a comma-separated list. | 1 |
| `Checked` | The checkbox field is checked. | 0 |
| `NotChecked` | The checkbox field is not checked. | 0 |
| `RadioOn` | The radio button is selected. | 0 |
| `RadioOff` | The radio button is not selected. | 0 |
| `IsEmpty` | The field is null or empty. | 0 |
| `IsNotEmpty` | The field is not null or empty. | 0 |

Common use cases are documented below. The examples assume the following profile configuration:

| Profile field group | Profile field | Value type |
|-|-|-|
| Favorites | Color | _Text_ |
| Favorites | Number | _Numeric_ |
| Favorites | Movie | _Text_ |

To select contacts whose favorite color is green:

```
"filter": {
  "segmentationFieldGroup": "Favorites",
  "segmentationField": "Color",
  "compareType": "Equals",
  "values": [
    {
      "value": "Green"
    }
  ]
}
```

To select contacts whose favorite color is green _and_ whose favorite number is between 10 and 20:

```
"filter": {
  filters: [
    {
      "compareType": "Equals",
      "segmentationFieldGroup": "Favorites",
      "segmentationField": "Color",
      "values": [
        {
          "value": "Green"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "compareType": "Between",
      "joinType": "And",
      "segmentationFieldGroup": "Favorites",
      "segmentationField": "Number",
      "values": [
        {
          "value": "10"
        },
        {
          "value": "20"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

To select contacts whose favorite color is red _or_ whose favorite number is 13:

```
"filter": {
  filters: [
    {
      "compareType": "Equals",
      "segmentationFieldGroup": "Favorites",
      "segmentationField": "Color",
      "values": [
        {
          "value": "Red"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "compareType": "Equals",
      "joinType": "Or",
      "segmentationFieldGroup": "Favorites",
      "segmentationField": "Number",
      "values": [
        {
          "value": "13"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

To select contacts whose favorite color is green, and additionally either has a favorite number of 13, or otherwise has a favorite movie containing the term `adventures`:

```
"filter": {
  filters: [
    {
      "compareType": "Equals",
      "segmentationFieldGroup": "Favorites",
      "segmentationField": "Color",
      "values": [
        {
          "value": "Green"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "joinType": "And"
      "filters": [
        {
          "compareType": "Equals",
          "segmentationFieldGroup": "Favorites",
          "segmentationField": "Number",
          "values": [
            {
              "value": "13"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "compareType": "Contains",
          "joinType": "Or"
          "segmentationFieldGroup": "Favorites",
          "segmentationField": "Movie",
          "values": [
            {
              "value": "adventures"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

To select contacts whose favorite color is either black, white, or gold:

```
"filter": {
  filters: [
    {
      "compareType": "InCommaList",
      "segmentationFieldGroup": "Favorites",
      "segmentationField": "Color",
      "values": [
        {
          "value": "Black,White,Gold"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

To select contacts who do not have a favorite color:

```
"filter": {
  filters: [
    {
      "compareType": "Empty",
      "segmentationFieldGroup": "Favorites",
      "segmentationField": "Color"
    }
  ]
}
```
